==English==

{{wikipedia}}

===Etymology===
From an idiomatic command sequence in the ''qed'' and ''ed'' text editors: "g/re/p", meaning: '''g'''lobally search for a [[regular expression]] ('''re''') and '''p'''rint.

===Noun===
'''grep'''
# a program which selects lines in a file which match a given pattern

===Verb===
# to use the program '''grep''' to search in a file
# by extension, to search anything (perhaps a paper document by eye)

===Derived terms===
*[[greppable]]

